[h3]Pop Raiding[/h3]
[list]
[*]Raiding bombardment no longer stops short of an empty planet. It abducts down to the last pop and the colony is destroyed with it.
[*]Pop raiding now works against every empire type, including fallen and awakened empires. Invasion, monthly auto-raids, and opportunistic authorization are no longer restricted to regular empires.
[*]Total war now authorizes raiding through every vector with no prompt and no Influence cost. Previously only bombardment and surrender captured pops in a total war, while invasion and monthly auto-raids did not.
[*]Driven Assimilators can now take the Raiding and Reaping casus belli. Total war empires were previously denied them.
[*]Reaping focus is available to gestalt empires with Nihilistic Acquisition, matching the documented behaviour.
[*]Nomad raiders now deliver captured pops to an arkship: the one in orbit of the raided planet, otherwise one in the same system, otherwise any arkship. Pops are delivered even if the arkship has no free housing.
[/list]

[h3]Plundering[/h3]
[list]
[*]Bombardment plundering now copies the loot instead of stealing it: the raider gains double the take, the target keeps their resources, and only the raider is notified.
[*]Invasion plunder raised to 18 months of output.
[/list]

[h3]Despoliation Traditions[/h3]
[list]
[*]Void Reaver pirate-waystation buff now adds a flat +1.5% collection, the same as a Reaver Stronghold.
[/list]

[h3]Fixes[/h3]
[list]
[*]The Steal Relic war goal no longer appears against targets that own no stealable relic, where winning the war would have stolen nothing.
[*]The bombardment plunder loot override now loads, so plundering uses the mod's loot behaviour instead of the vanilla one.
[/list]

[h3]Compatibility[/h3]
[list]
[*]Updated for Stellaris 4.4.4.
[/list]
